sentences.content: Scene narrative progressions let the user describe complex scenes by decomposing it into simpler subscenes.
Making his lunch
The boy has short, black hair.
He is wearing a yellow and white striped shirt.
He is getting hungry.
Finding ingredients for lunch
The boy has peanut butter.
He has jelly made from fruit juice and sugar.
He has bread made from whole wheat flour.
He has a bowl of fruit with apple, orange, banana, and grapes.
Making a sandwich
The boy places two slices of bread on his plate.
The boy is spreading peanut butter on the bread.
The boy will spread jelly on his sandwich.
